<h2 id="regulamentacao-e-seguranca" class="contentIndexTitle">Regulation & Security&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-success badge-pill">&#10003; Good</span></h2>
<h3 class="contentIndexSubTitle">XM operates under multiple financial regulators, ensuring transparency and trader protection.</h3>
<p>Founded in 2009, XM is operated by Trading Point Holdings Ltd and regulated by several international authorities, including CySEC (Cyprus Securities and Exchange Commission), ASIC (Australian Securities and Investments Commission), and IFSC in Belize. These regulatory frameworks require strict compliance standards such as segregated client funds, risk management policies, and transparent operations. With millions of traders across more than 190 countries, XM has built a strong reputation in the global Forex industry.</p>
<br>

<h2 id="plataformas-de-negociacao" class="contentIndexTitle">Trading Platforms&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-success badge-pill">&#10003; Good</span></h2>
<h3 class="contentIndexSubTitle">Industry-leading MetaTrader platforms with powerful tools and cross-device compatibility.</h3>
<p>XM offers both MetaTrader 4 (MT4) and MetaTrader 5 (MT5), two of the most widely used trading platforms in the world. These platforms provide advanced charting tools, dozens of technical indicators, automated trading through Expert Advisors (EAs), and flexible order execution options. Traders can access the platform through desktop applications (Windows and macOS), web browser terminals, and mobile apps for iOS and Android.</p>
<br>

<h2 id="spreads-e-comissoes" class="contentIndexTitle">Spreads & Commissions&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-success badge-pill">&#10003; Good</span></h2>
<h3 class="contentIndexSubTitle">Competitive spreads with no hidden costs and flexible account types.</h3>
<p>XM offers several account types with different pricing models. Standard and Micro accounts operate with spreads only, while Ultra Low accounts provide tighter spreads for more active traders. The broker generally does not charge deposit or withdrawal fees, though third-party payment providers may apply their own charges. An inactivity fee may apply if an account remains dormant for a long period.</p>
<br>

<h2 id="tipos-de-conta" class="contentIndexTitle">Account Types&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-success badge-pill">&#10003; Good</span></h2>
<h3 class="contentIndexSubTitle">Multiple account options to suit beginners, active traders, and Islamic finance requirements.</h3>
<p>XM offers Micro, Standard, Ultra Low, and Shares accounts. Micro and Standard accounts are ideal for beginners and casual traders, while the Ultra Low account targets more active traders seeking tighter spreads. XM also provides a Swap-Free (Islamic) account for traders who require compliance with Sharia law. Each account type is available on both MT4 and MT5.</p>
<br>

<h2 id="pares-de-moedas-e-instrumentos" class="contentIndexTitle">Currency Pairs & Instruments&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-success badge-pill">&#10003; Good</span></h2>
<h3 class="contentIndexSubTitle">Broad range of Forex pairs alongside CFDs on commodities, stocks, and indices.</h3>
<p>XM provides access to more than 1,000 trading instruments. Forex traders can trade major, minor, and exotic currency pairs with competitive spreads. In addition to Forex, the broker offers CFDs on commodities such as gold and oil, stock indices, shares from global markets, and cryptocurrencies depending on the jurisdiction. This wide asset selection allows traders to diversify their strategies across multiple markets.</p>
<br>

<h2 id="alavancagem-e-margem" class="contentIndexTitle">Leverage & Margin&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-warning badge-pill">&#9888; Average</span></h2>
<h3 class="contentIndexSubTitle">High leverage available in some jurisdictions, but significantly restricted for retail clients under top-tier regulators.</h3>
<p>XM offers leverage of up to 1:1000 for clients under its IFSC (Belize) entity, which may appeal to traders seeking higher exposure. However, clients regulated under CySEC or ASIC are capped at 1:30 for major Forex pairs in line with ESMA and ASIC retail leverage rules. This means the effective leverage available depends heavily on which regulatory entity your account falls under. XM does apply negative balance protection across all accounts, ensuring traders cannot lose more than their deposited funds — but the inconsistency in leverage access across jurisdictions makes this a mixed picture overall.</p>
<br>

<h2 id="depositos-e-saques" class="contentIndexTitle">Deposits & Withdrawals&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-success badge-pill">&#10003; Good</span></h2>
<h3 class="contentIndexSubTitle">Multiple global payment methods and a low minimum deposit of just $5.</h3>
<p>XM supports several payment options including credit and debit cards (Visa and Mastercard), e-wallets such as Skrill and Neteller, and international bank transfers. The minimum deposit is only <strong>$5</strong>, making the platform accessible to new traders who want to start with a small amount of capital. Withdrawals are typically processed within 24 hours on the broker's side, although the final processing time depends on the payment provider.</p>
<br>

<h2 id="pesquisa-e-analise" class="contentIndexTitle">Research & Analysis&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-success badge-pill">&#10003; Good</span></h2>
<h3 class="contentIndexSubTitle">Daily market analysis, economic calendar, and trading signals to support decision-making.</h3>
<p>XM provides daily technical and fundamental market analysis covering major Forex pairs, commodities, and indices. Traders have access to an economic calendar that highlights key macroeconomic events and their potential market impact. The broker also offers trading signals and market updates through its platform and website, helping traders stay informed and make more confident decisions.</p>
<br>

<h2 id="conta-demo" class="contentIndexTitle">Demo Account&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-success badge-pill">&#10003; Good</span></h2>
<h3 class="contentIndexSubTitle">Unlimited demo accounts with virtual funds to practice trading strategies.</h3>
<p>XM offers free demo accounts that simulate real market conditions using virtual funds. Traders can practice on MT4 or MT5 while learning how the platform works and testing trading strategies. Demo balances can be reset, allowing users to continue practicing without financial risk. This feature is especially useful for beginners learning how Forex markets operate.</p>
